oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cadet 2nd Lieutenant receiving an award
Cadet Second Lieutenant receiving an award
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Cadet 2nd Lt. Paul W. Landers of Murfreesboro receiving an award on May 10, 1966. He received the "Superior Cadet Award" for the junior class, presented by Dean Firman Cunningham, head of the School of Business and Industry at Middle Tennessee State University. Landers also received a commendation ribbon and the Association of the United States Army medal as the most outstanding cadet in the 2nd Battalion.
Paul W. Landers; Dean Firman Cunningham

Middle Tennessee State University May 10, 1966 Murfreesboro
CUT LINES
Cadet 2nd Lt. Paul W. Landers of Murfreesboro is shown receiving the "Superior Cadet Award" for the junior class, being presented by Dean Firman Cunningham, head of the School of Business and Industry at Middle Tennessee State University. Mr. Landers also received the Association of the United States Army medal as the most outstanding cadet in the second battalion. He also received a commendation ribbon. Cadet Landers is the son of Mr. and Mrs. W.E. Landers of 110 Gayle Lane in Murfreesboro.
